","1364":"1364","7 août 1338":"7 augustus 1338","Châtelain, Anjou, France":"Châtelain, Anjou, Frankrijk","Ligny et Barrois, Meuse, Lorraine, France":"Meuse, Lorraine, Frankrijk","Lille, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Lille, Noorderdepartement, Hauts-de-France, Frankrijk","Phalempin, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Phalempin, Noorderdepartement, Hauts-de-France, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1280–7 août 1338":"1280–7 August 1338","1280–1338":"1280–1338","1275–1354":"1275–1354","1313–1364":"1313–1364","1258–1291":"1258–1291","1256–1320":"1256–1320","before 5 November 1305":"before 5 November 1305","14 September 1320":"14 September 1320","before November 1279":"before November 1279","1275":"1275","1280":"1280","1291":"1291","1338":"1338","1313":"1313","1258":"1258","8 août 1338":"8 August 1338","1256":"1256","1354":"1354","1320":"1320","1364":"1364","7 août 1338":"7 August 1338","Châtelain, Anjou, France":"Châtelain, Anjou, France","Ligny et Barrois, Meuse, Lorraine, France":"Meuse, Lorraine, France","Lille, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Lille, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France","Phalempin, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Phalempin, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Lille","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Danish: from the Old Norse personal name <i>Bille</i> meaning ‘axe, hatchet’.","German (mainly North Rhine-Westphalia) and Danish (of German origin): nickname for someone with a conspicuous bottom, from Middle Low German <i>bille</i> ‘buttock’.","French, Walloon, and Flemish: from Old French <i>bille</i> ‘block, piece of tree trunk; stick, plank’ (a word of Gaulish origin), probably used as a metonymic occupational name for a sawyer or a carpenter, joiner."],"variants":[{"name":"Billa","meanings":["Italian (Sicily): probably of French origin (see   Bille  ).","Hispanic: altered form of Spanish   Villa  .","Slovak and Czech (<b>Billá</b>): feminine form (denoting ‘the daughter, or wife of’) of <b>Billý</b> (see   Billy  )."]},{"name":"Billeaud","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Raoul, Andre, Jacques, Marcelle.","French: variant of <b>Billaud</b>, which is from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Biliwald</i>, composed of the elements <i>bili</i> ‘gentle’ and <i>wald</i> ‘power, authority’, or a derivative of Old French <i>bille</i> ‘block, piece of tree trunk; stick’ (see   Bille  ).","History: Pierre-Jean Billaud/Billeaud from Bourgneuf-en-Retz in Loire-Atlantique, Brittany (France), married Rosalie-Félicité Grizeau in Bourgneuf-en-Retz <i>c.</i> 1832, died in Lafayette Parish, LA, in 1877."]}]},{"name":"Guyotte","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of American French   Goyette  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Guyett","meanings":["American French: variant of   Guyette  ."]},{"name":"Goyette","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Normand, Armand, Marcel, Aime, Emile, Philippe, Martial, Monique, Raoul, Alain, Alcide, Alexandre.","Americanized form of French <b>Goguet</b>: nickname for a cheerful or mocking person, derived from Old French <i>gogue</i> ‘joke, mockery’. Altered ending reflects the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>. Compare   Guyett   and   Guyette  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guyotte de Lille was born in 1280, in Lille, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France, her father, Jean Chatelain IV, was 23 and her mother, Beatrix of Clermont, was 24. She married Waleran II de Luxembourg before 5 November 1305. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 7 August 1338, in Phalempin, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 58, and was buried in Phalempin, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France."},"et":{"1280–7 août 1338":"1280–7. august 1338","1280–1338":"1280–1338","1275–1354":"1275–1354","1313–1364":"1313–1364","1258–1291":"1258–1291","1256–1320":"1256–1320","before 5 November 1305":"enne 5. novembrit 1305","14 September 1320":"14. september 1320","before November 1279":"enne novembrit 1279","1275":"1275","1280":"1280","1291":"1291","1338":"1338","1313":"1313","1258":"1258","8 août 1338":"8. august 1338","1256":"1256","1354":"1354","1320":"1320","1364":"1364","7 août 1338":"7. august 1338","Châtelain, Anjou, France":"Châtelain, Anjou, Prantsusmaa","Ligny et Barrois, Meuse, Lorraine, France":"Meuse, Lorraine, Prantsusmaa","Lille, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Lille, Nord, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Phalempin, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Phalempin, Nord, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1280–7 août 1338":"1280–7. elokuuta 1338","1280–1338":"1280–1338","1275–1354":"1275–1354","1313–1364":"1313–1364","1258–1291":"1258–1291","1256–1320":"1256–1320","before 5 November 1305":"ennen vuotta 5. marraskuuta 1305","14 September 1320":"14. syyskuuta 1320","before November 1279":"ennen vuotta marraskuu 1279","1275":"1275","1280":"1280","1291":"1291","1338":"1338","1313":"1313","1258":"1258","8 août 1338":"8. elokuuta 1338","1256":"1256","1354":"1354","1320":"1320","1364":"1364","7 août 1338":"7. elokuuta 1338","Châtelain, Anjou, France":"Châtelain, Anjou, Ranska","Ligny et Barrois, Meuse, Lorraine, France":"Meuse, Lorraine, Ranska","Lille, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Lille, Nord, H